{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the responsibilities of COMPANY in supporting Bravatek, but lacks clarity on financial obligations and potential liabilities for non-operator participation.",
  "operative_text": "COMPANY agrees to use its best efforts to promote and support project lead finding and after-sales support of Bravatek by: a. Listing Bravatek in all appropriate sales and marketing materials as a non-exclusive alliance partner (with focus of government customers) b. Provide timely responses to both technical and administrative questions posed by Bravatek. c. Promote Bravatek's product and service offerings whenever possible. d. Aid Bravatek in the writing of any technical/marketing/sales documents when requested and participate in mutually-agreed upon sales calls. e. Provide Bravatek with co-branded marketing material that can be emailed or handed to prospective clients.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on financial obligations for COMPANY's support of Bravatek, particularly regarding potential liabilities and the scope of non-operator involvement in such activities. ",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines joint development and marketing obligations, but lacks clarity on financial responsibilities and risk allocation in case of disputes.",
  "operative_text": "Bravatek and COMPANY agree to jointly: a. Develop and implement a joint Product Solution and Application Strategy whereby targeted markets/potential client- types/applications are mutually agreed upon; b. Support each other in all agreed-upon technical, marketing and promotional efforts; c. Develop a joint strategy for developing new product/services/capabilities to mutually benefit both parties; d. Utilize each other as Preferred Vendors for services whenever possible upon mutual agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on financial responsibilities and risk allocation in case of disputes, particularly regarding joint development costs and potential liabilities.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause lacks clarity on the mechanics of compensation for sales, particularly regarding lead-finder fees and payment terms. This could lead to disputes and financial uncertainty.",
  "operative_text": "When custom Products are designed, developed and to be delivered to Bravatek-identified perspective clients, the parties shall agree to a proposed sales price for use during the project in writing prior to the commencement of each project. For any Product or Solution sold to any perspective clients introduced by Bravatek registered with COMPANY via email to COMPANY's CEO and delivered through Bravatek or a COMPANY-designated distribution affiliate(s) or sales channel(s), Bravatek will receive a lead-finder fee, to be mutually discussed and finally decided by COMPANY at the range of minimum of 10% to maximum of 20% of project revenue, with an exact fee to be depending upon the overall project sales margin and cost of development and delivery of each project, payable NET 30 days after each client payment on delivered products received at COMPANY's bank account.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on the mechanics of compensation for sales, particularly regarding lead-finder fees and payment terms. This could lead to disputes and financial uncertainty.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 4"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines 'Confidential Information' but lacks clarity on how it will be handled in the event of a termination and potential disputes over its use.",
  "operative_text": "‘Confidential information’ shall mean any and all technical and non-technical information, documents and materials related to client projects of party and products, services and business of each of the parties. COMPANY and Bravatek agree to maintain in strict confidence and not to disclose or disseminate, or to use for any purposes other than performance of the projects, the Confidential Information disclosed.  The obligation of non-disclosure shall not apply to the following:   a. Information at or after such time that is publicly available through no fault of either party   b. Information at or after such time that is disclosed to either party by a third party entitled to disclose such information   c. Information which is required by law to be disclosed to federal, state or local authorities.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how confidential information will be handled in the event of a termination and potential disputes over its use.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 5"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines confidentiality obligations for a period after termination, but lacks specifics on how confidential information will be handled or what constitutes 'reasonable precaution' and 'reasonable efforts'. This could lead to disputes regarding the scope and enforcement of confidentiality.",
  "operative_text": "For a period of five (5) years after termination of this Agreement, the parties shall treat as confidential all information and take every reasonable precaution and use all reasonable efforts to prevent the unauthorized disclosure of the same. The parties agree to take all steps reasonably necessary and appropriate to ensure that their employees, agents, and/or assistants treat all information as confidential and to ensure that such employees, agents, and/or assistants are familiar with and abide by the terms of this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks specifics on how confidential information will be handled or what constitutes 'reasonable precaution' and 'reasonable efforts'. This could lead to disputes regarding the scope and enforcement of confidentiality.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["5 years", "parties", "information", "reasonable precaution", "reasonable efforts"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause sets a fixed term for the agreement and outlines automatic renewal, but lacks clarity on how capital calls or participant withdrawals will be handled upon termination.",
  "operative_text": "The term of this Agreement is twelve (12) months from the date hereof, and will be automatically renewed for one (1) additional twelve month period unless either party shall notify the other in writing of its intention not to renew. Such notice must be given ninety (90) days prior to expiration of the original term. This Agreement may also be terminated by either party upon ninety (90) days written notice.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The agreement lacks clarity on how capital calls or participant withdrawals will be handled upon termination.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["termination", "capital call mechanics", "participant withdrawals"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "The clause lacks clarity on how notices are delivered, potentially leading to disputes regarding communication and obligations.",
  "operative_text": "Any notices required under this Agreement shall be delivered to:   Bravatek Technologies, Inc. 2028 E. Ben White Blvd., Unit #240-2835 Austin, Texas 78741   Sibannac, Inc. 2122 E Highland Avenue, STE 425 Phoenix, AZ 85016\n",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how notices are delivered, potentially leading to disputes regarding communication and obligations.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 8"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause establishes joint and several indemnification for both parties, potentially exposing the non-operator to significant financial risk in case of negligence or misconduct by the other party.",
  "operative_text": "10) Indemnification   COMPANY shall indemnify Bravatek, its directors, officers and employees, for any and all damages, costs, expenses, and other liabilities, including reasonable attorney's fees and court costs incurred in connection with any third-party claim, action or proceeding arising from the negligence or intentional misconduct of COMPANY or breach of COMPANY of any of its obligations under this Agreement.   Bravatek shall indemnify COMPANY, its directors, officers and employees, for any and all damages, costs, expenses, and other liabilities, including reasonable attorney's fees and court costs, incurred in connection with any third-party claim, action or proceeding arising from the negligence or intentional misconduct of Bravatek or breach of Bravatek of any of its obligations under this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause establishes joint and several indemnification for both parties, potentially exposing the non-operator to significant financial risk in case of negligence or misconduct by the other party.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["COMPANY", "Bravatek"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause limits modification to the agreement, potentially hindering necessary adjustments or clarifications during the JV's lifecycle.",
  "operative_text": "No changes or modifications of this Agreement or any of its terms shall be deemed effective unless in writing and executed by the parties hereto.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause limits modification to the agreement, potentially hindering necessary adjustments or clarifications during the JV's lifecycle.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["clause 11"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause restricts assignment of the joint venture agreement, potentially hindering flexibility and limiting Acme Holdings' ability to transfer its stake in the JV.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement shall not be assignable by either party without the prior written consent of the other party.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause restricts assignment of the joint venture agreement, potentially hindering flexibility and limiting Acme Holdings' ability to transfer its stake in the JV.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["This Agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause asserts the complete agreement between parties and supersedes all prior negotiations or agreements. It also clarifies that the agreement is not effective until signed by both parties.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement represents the complete and entire understanding between the parties regarding the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, or agreements, either written or oral, regarding this subject matter. This Agreement shall not be considered accepted, approved or otherwise effective until signed by the appropriate parties.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause states that the agreement is complete and final, superseding all prior negotiations, representations, or agreements. This could potentially limit Acme Holdings' ability to negotiate for favorable terms in future discussions with the operator regarding capital calls, asset distribution, or other critical aspects of the joint venture.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["This Agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

